with Uncle Fred.

350
00:16:02,400 --> 00:16:03,470
Uncle Fred?

351
00:16:03,530 --> 00:16:04,900
Is that the only man left?

352
00:16:04,970 --> 00:16:06,610
Well, there's cousin Trudy.

353
00:16:06,670 --> 00:16:09,840
She's pre-op, but she's
wearing a very nice tux.

354
00:16:09,910 --> 00:16:13,250
Why can't I just walk down
the aisle with Charlie?
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

355
00:16:13,310 --> 00:16:15,420
Whoa, I'm just an innocent
bystander at this shindig.

356
00:16:15,480 --> 00:16:17,350
Oh, come on, picture
the look on Judith's face

357
00:16:17,410 --> 00:16:18,610
when she sees you
at the altar.

358
00:16:18,680 --> 00:16:20,780
I'm in.

359
00:16:21,880 --> 00:16:24,420
Oh, God.

360
00:16:26,320 --> 00:16:27,750
(whispers):
Herb. Herb.

361
00:16:27,820 --> 00:16:30,490
Oh, hi. Hey, thanks
for bringing him down.

362
00:16:30,560 --> 00:16:32,270
Well, you look
very handsome, Jake.

363
00:16:32,330 --> 00:16:34,230
I know. It's the tux.

364
00:16:34,300 --> 00:16:35,770
Okay, well, uh,
congratulations.

365
00:16:35,830 --> 00:16:37,760
I wish you both a
lot of happiness.

366
00:16:37,830 --> 00:16:39,300
Oh, thanks, Al.

367
00:16:39,370 --> 00:16:40,610
Don't make the same
mistakes I did.

368
00:16:40,670 --> 00:16:43,340
I won't— she wrote
them down for me.

369
00:16:43,410 --> 00:16:47,450
Good. All right, buddy,
uh, have some fun.
Okay.

370
00:16:48,780 --> 00:16:51,850
Oh. Remember,
that tux is a rental.

371
00:16:53,420 --> 00:16:54,720
Excuse me.

372
00:16:54,780 --> 00:16:56,750
